\par Check once per hour (or portion of an hour) spent in local or overland movement to see if travelers have become lost. In the case of a party moving together, only the character leading the way makes the check.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effects of Being Lost:}{\fs20\cf0  If a party becomes lost
, it is no longer certain of moving in the direction it intended to travel. Randomly determine the direction in which the party actually travels during each hour of local or overland movement. The characters\rquote 
 movement continues to be random until they blunder into a landmark they can\rquote t miss, or until they recognize that they are lost and make an effort to regain their bearings.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Recognizing that You\rquote re Lost:}{\fs20\cf0  Once per hour of random travel, each character in the party may attempt a Survival check (DC 20, \endash 1 p
er hour of random travel) to recognize that they are no longer certain of their direction of travel. Some circumstances may make it obvious that the characters are lost.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Setting a New Course: }{\fs20\cf0 A lost party is also uncertain of determining in which direction
 it should travel in order to reach a desired objective. Determining the correct direction of travel once a party has become lost requires a Survival check (DC 15, +2 per hour of random travel). If a character fails this check, he chooses a random directi
on as the \'93correct\'94 direction for resuming travel.
\par Once the characters are traveling along their new course, correct or incorrect, they may get lost again. If the conditions still make it possible for travelers to become lost, check once per hour of travel 
as described in Chance to Get Lost, above, to see if the party maintains its new course or begins to move at random again.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Conflicting Directions: }{\fs20\cf0 It\rquote s possible that several characters may attempt to determine the right direction to proceed after becoming 
lost. Make a Survival check for each character in secret, then tell the players whose characters succeeded the correct direction in which to travel, and tell the players whose characters failed a random direction they think is right. 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Regaining Your Bearings:}{\fs20\cf0  There are several ways to become un-lost. First, if the characters successfully set a new course and follow it to the destination they\rquote re trying to reach, they\rquote 
re not lost anymore. Second, the characters through random movement might run into an unmistakable landmark. Third, if conditions suddenly improve\emdash the fog lifts or the sun comes up\emdash 
lost characters may attempt to set a new course, as described above, with a +4 bonus on the Survival check. Finally, magic may make their course clear.
