\par }{\fs20\cf0 Sometimes weather can play an important role in an adventure.
\par Table: Random Weather is an appropriate weather table for general use, and can be used as a basis for a local weather tables. Terms on that table are defined as follows.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Calm:}{\fs20\cf0  Wind speeds are light (0 to 10 mph).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Cold:}{\fs20\cf0  Between 0\'b0 and 40\'b0 Fahrenheit during the day, 10 to 20 degrees colder at night.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Cold Snap: }{\fs20\cf0 Lowers temperature by \endash 10\'b0 F.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Downpour:}{\fs20\cf0  Treat as rain (see Precipitation, below), but conceals as fog. Can create floods (see above). A downpour lasts for 2d4 hours.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Heat Wave:}{\fs20\cf0  Raises temperature by +10\'b0 F.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Hot:}{\fs20\cf0  Between 85\'b0 and 110\'b0 Fahrenheit during the day, 10 to 20 degrees colder at night.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Moderate:}{\fs20\cf0  Between 40\'b0 and 60\'b0 Fahrenheit during the day, 10 to 20 degrees colder at night.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Powerful Storm }{\b\i\fs20\cf0 (Windstorm/Blizzard/Hurricane/Tornado): }{\fs20\cf0 Wind speeds are over 50 mph (see Table: Wind Effects). In addition, blizzards are accompanied 
by heavy snow (1d3 feet), and hurricanes are accompanied by downpours (see above). Windstorms last for 1d6 hours. Blizzards last for 1d3 days. Hurricanes can last for up to a week, but their major impact on characters will come in a 24-to-48-hour period w
hen the center of the storm moves through their area. Tornadoes are very short-lived (1d6\'d710 minutes), typically forming as part of a thunderstorm system. }{\fs21\cf0 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Precipitation:}{\fs20\cf0  Roll d% to determine whether the precipitation is fog (01\endash 30), rain/snow (31\endash 90), or sleet/hail (91\endash 00). Snow and sleet occur only when the temperature is 30\'b0
 Fahrenheit or below. Most precipitation lasts for 2d4 hours. By contrast, hail lasts for only 1d20 minutes but usually accompanies 1d4 hours of rain.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Storm }{\b\i\fs20\cf0 (Duststorm/Snowstorm/Thunderstorm):}{\i\fs20\cf0  }{\fs20\cf0 Wind speeds are severe (30 to 50 mph) and visibility is cut by three-quarters. Storms last for 2d4\endash 1 hours. See Storms, below, for more details. 

\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Warm:}{\fs20\cf0  Between 60\'b0 and 85\'b0 Fahrenheit during the day, 10 to 20 degrees colder at night.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Windy:}{\fs20\cf0  Wind speeds are moderate to strong (10 to 30 mph); see Table: Wind Effects on the following page.
