\par }{\fs20\cf0 Just as characters take damage when they fall more than 10 feet, so too do they take damage when they are hit by falling objects.
\par Objects that fall upon characters deal damage based on their weight and the distance they have fallen.
\par For each 200 pounds of an object\rquote s 
weight, the object deals 1d6 points of damage, provided it falls at least 10 feet. Distance also comes into play, adding an additional 1d6 points of damage for every 10-foot increment it falls beyond the first (to a maximum of 20d6 points of damage).

